==English==

===Noun===
'''category''' (''plural:'' '''categories''')

# A [[group]], often [[name]]d or [[number]]ed, to which items are [[assign]]ed based on [[similarity]] or defined [[criteria]].
#: ''This steep and dangerous climb belongs to the most difficult '''category'''.''
#: ''I wouldn't put this book in the same '''category''' as the author's first novel.''
# (''mathematics'') A [[collection]] of [[objects]], together with a [[transitive]]ly [[closed]] [[collection]] of [[composable]] [[arrows]] between them, such that every object has an [[identity]] arrow.
#: ''One well-known '''category''' has sets as objects and continuous functions as arrows.''

